        "remove_horizontal_spacing": true,
        "liquid": "<style>\n  .sorelya-faq,\n  .sorelya-faq * {\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq {\n    width: 100%;\n    padding: 60px 22px;\n    background: #ffffff;\n    color: #111111;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__inner {\n    width: 100%;\n    max-width: 1180px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n  }\n\n  /* =========================\n     HEADER\n  ========================= */\n\n  .sorelya-faq__heading {\n    max-width: 850px;\n    margin: 0 auto 14px;\n    color: #050505;\n    font-size: clamp(34px, 4.5vw, 62px);\n    font-weight: 900;\n    line-height: 1.03;\n    text-align: center;\n    letter-spacing: -0.045em;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__subheading {\n    max-width: 650px;\n    margin: 0 auto 38px;\n    color: #686868;\n    font-size: 16px;\n    font-weight: 400;\n    line-height: 1.55;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n\n  /* =========================\n     FAQ LIST\n  ========================= */\n\n  .sorelya-faq__list {\n    width: 100%;\n    border-top: 1px solid #dedede;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__item {\n    border-bottom: 1px solid #dedede;\n    background: #ffffff;\n  }\n\n  /* =========================\n     QUESTION\n  ========================= */\n\n  .sorelya-faq__trigger {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: space-between;\n    gap: 20px;\n    width: 100%;\n    padding: 22px 4px;\n    border: 0;\n    background: transparent;\n    color: #111111;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    text-align: left;\n    cursor: pointer;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__question {\n    flex: 1;\n    color: #111111;\n    font-size: 17px;\n    font-weight: 800;\n    line-height: 1.35;\n    letter-spacing: -0.015em;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__plus {\n    position: relative;\n    flex: 0 0 auto;\n    width: 20px;\n    height: 20px;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__plus::before,\n  .sorelya-faq__plus::after {\n    content: \"\";\n    position: absolute;\n    top: 50%;\n    left: 50%;\n    width: 16px;\n    height: 2px;\n    border-radius: 999px;\n    background: #111111;\n    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);\n    transition: transform 0.25s ease;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__plus::after {\n    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(90deg);\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__item.open .sorelya-faq__plus::after {\n    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(0deg);\n  }\n\n  /* =========================\n     ANSWER\n  ========================= */\n\n  .sorelya-faq__answer {\n    display: none;\n    padding: 0 48px 24px 4px;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__item.open .sorelya-faq__answer {\n    display: block;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__answer p {\n    max-width: 940px;\n    margin: 0;\n    color: #555555;\n    font-size: 15px;\n    font-weight: 400;\n    line-height: 1.7;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__answer strong {\n    color: #111111;\n    font-weight: 800;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-faq__note {\n    display: block;\n    max-width: 940px;\n    margin-top: 13px;\n    padding: 12px 14px;\n    border-left: 3px solid #b88c66;\n    background: #f7f5f3;\n    color: #373737;\n    font-size: 13px;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    line-height: 1.55;\n  }\n\n  /* =========================\n     INGREDIENT TABLE\n  ========================= */\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients {\n    width: 100%;\n    margin-top: 18px;\n    overflow-x: auto;\n    border: 1px solid #dedede;\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    scrollbar-width: thin;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients table {\n    width: 100%;\n    min-width: 760px;\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    background: #ffffff;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients th,\n  .sorelya-ingredients td {\n    padding: 13px 14px;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid #e4e4e4;\n    border-right: 1px solid #e4e4e4;\n    color: #333333;\n    font-size: 13px;\n    line-height: 1.45;\n    text-align: left;\n    vertical-align: top;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients th:last-child,\n  .sorelya-ingredients td:last-child {\n    border-right: 0;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients tr:last-child td {\n    border-bottom: 0;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients th {\n    background: #f5f5f5;\n    color: #111111;\n    font-size: 12px;\n    font-weight: 800;\n    letter-spacing: 0.02em;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n  }\n\n  .sorelya-ingredients td strong {\n    color: #111111;\n  }\n\n  /* =========================\n     MOBILE\n  ========================= */\n\n  @media (max-width: 749px) {\n    .sorelya-faq {\n      padding: 42px 16px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__heading {\n      max-width: 340px;\n      font-size: 31px;\n      line-height: 1.05;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__subheading {\n      max-width: 340px;\n      margin-bottom: 28px;\n      font-size: 14px;\n      line-height: 1.5;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__trigger {\n      gap: 14px;\n      padding: 18px 2px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__question {\n      font-size: 15px;\n      line-height: 1.4;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__plus {\n      width: 18px;\n      height: 18px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__plus::before,\n    .sorelya-faq__plus::after {\n      width: 14px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__answer {\n      padding: 0 28px 20px 2px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__answer p {\n      font-size: 13.5px;\n      line-height: 1.62;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-faq__note {\n      font-size: 12px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-ingredients {\n      width: calc(100vw - 34px);\n      margin-top: 16px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-ingredients th,\n    .sorelya-ingredients td {\n      padding: 11px 12px;\n      font-size: 12px;\n    }\n\n    .sorelya-ingredients th {\n      font-size: 11px;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n\n<section class=\"sorelya-faq\" data-sorelya-faq>\n  <div class=\"sorelya-faq__inner\">\n\n    <h2 class=\"sorelya-faq__heading\">\n      Your Questions, Answered\n    </h2>\n\n    <p class=\"sorelya-faq__subheading\">\n      Everything you need to know before trying SORELYA on your own lips.\n    </p>\n\n    <div class=\"sorelya-faq__list\">\n\n      <!-- FAQ 1 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            How does SORELYA find my shade?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            SORELYA starts almost clear, then gradually develops over your\n            natural lip color. The finished tint may look softer, warmer or\n            deeper depending on your lips, creating a\n            <strong>personalized-looking result without choosing from a shade chart.</strong>\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 2 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            Is it made for mature lips?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Yes. SORELYA was created with mature lips in mind. Its smooth,\n            balm-like texture is intended to feel more comfortable than heavy\n            matte formulas that can emphasize dryness, texture and fine lines.\n          </p>\n\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__note\">\n            Your lips changed. Your lipstick should too.\n          </span>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 3 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            Can I use it if my lips are very dry?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Yes. Apply SORELYA to clean, smooth lips. If your lips are severely\n            chapped or peeling, apply a small amount of balm first, allow it to\n            absorb, then gently blot away the excess before applying SORELYA.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 4 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            Will the color settle into my lip lines?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            SORELYA is designed to help the tint remain on your lips instead of\n            visibly feathering into the fine lines around your mouth. For the\n            cleanest result, use one thin, even layer and let the color develop\n            before applying more.\n          </p>\n\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__note\">\n            Color that stays on your lips—not in your lip lines.\n          </span>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 5 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            What color will it become on me?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Results can vary from woman to woman. SORELYA may develop into a\n            soft rose, a warmer pink-coral or a deeper berry-pink depending on\n            your natural lip tone and individual lip chemistry.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 6 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            Does it work on every skin tone?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            SORELYA can be worn across fair, medium and deep complexions.\n            Because the tint develops over your existing lip color, the same\n            tube may produce a slightly different-looking result on each woman.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 7 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            Can I make the color more intense?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Yes. Begin with one light layer and allow the tint to develop. Add a\n            second thin layer for a slightly deeper-looking result. Building\n            the color gradually gives you more control over the intensity.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 8 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            How long does the color last?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            SORELYA is designed to keep the tint looking soft and even for\n            hours. Wear time can vary depending on meals, oils, drinks and your\n            natural lip chemistry. Reapply whenever you want to refresh or\n            deepen the color.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 9 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            What ingredients does SORELYA contain?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            The formula is presented as containing the ingredients below.\n            Because the supplier has not yet provided the complete official\n            INCI label, the corresponding INCI names listed here are\n            <strong>probable names and not a final verified ingredient declaration.</strong>\n          </p>\n\n          <div class=\"sorelya-ingredients\">\n            <table>\n              <thead>\n                <tr>\n                  <th>Presented ingredient</th>\n                  <th>Probable INCI name</th>\n                  <th>Purpose in the formula</th>\n                </tr>\n              </thead>\n\n              <tbody>\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Petroleum jelly</td>\n                  <td><strong>Petrolatum</strong></td>\n                  <td>Occlusive agent that helps reduce moisture loss.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Mineral oil</td>\n                  <td><strong>Paraffinum Liquidum / Mineral Oil</strong></td>\n                  <td>Emollient and texture-enhancing ingredient.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Beeswax</td>\n                  <td><strong>Cera Alba / Beeswax</strong></td>\n                  <td>Provides structure to the stick and helps protect lips.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Vitamin E</td>\n                  <td><strong>Tocopherol or Tocopheryl Acetate</strong></td>\n                  <td>Antioxidant and lip-conditioning ingredient.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Hyaluronic acid</td>\n                  <td><strong>Hyaluronic Acid or Sodium Hyaluronate</strong></td>\n                  <td>Humectant. The exact form has not been specified.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>24-karat gold</td>\n                  <td><strong>Gold / CI 77480</strong></td>\n                  <td>Provides the visible golden effect inside the lipstick.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Shea butter</td>\n                  <td><strong>Butyrospermum Parkii Butter</strong></td>\n                  <td>Nourishing emollient that helps soften the lips.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Jojoba oil</td>\n                  <td><strong>Simmondsia Chinensis Seed Oil</strong></td>\n                  <td>Emollient and conditioning oil.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Unspecified oils</td>\n                  <td><strong>Not currently identified</strong></td>\n                  <td>Used for moisture, glide and texture.</td>\n                </tr>\n\n                <tr>\n                  <td>Color-adaptive pigments</td>\n                  <td><strong>Not currently identified</strong></td>\n                  <td>Responsible for the developing pink or coral tint.</td>\n                </tr>\n              </tbody>\n            </table>\n          </div>\n\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__note\">\n            The complete official INCI list printed on the product packaging\n            should be treated as the final ingredient reference.\n          </span>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 10 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            Is it suitable for sensitive lips?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Sensitivities differ from person to person. Review the complete\n            ingredient label before use, perform a patch test and discontinue\n            use if irritation occurs. Consult a qualified professional if you\n            have a known allergy or recurring lip condition.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 11 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            How do I remove it?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Use your usual lip makeup remover, cleansing balm or oil-based\n            cleanser. Massage gently and wipe the color away without harsh\n            rubbing or pulling on delicate lips.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 12 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            What if I do not love my shade?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Your purchase is protected by our\n            <strong>60-day money-back guarantee.</strong> Try SORELYA on your\n            own lips and see how the tint develops. If it is not right for you,\n            contact our support team within 60 days of receiving your order.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- FAQ 13 -->\n      <article class=\"sorelya-faq__item\" data-sorelya-faq-item>\n        <button class=\"sorelya-faq__trigger\" type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__question\">\n            How does shipping work?\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"sorelya-faq__plus\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </button>\n\n        <div class=\"sorelya-faq__answer\">\n          <p>\n            Every order includes <strong>free tracked shipping.</strong> Once\n            your order leaves our warehouse, you will receive an email\n            containing your tracking information. Delivery times may vary\n            depending on your location.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    document.querySelectorAll('[data-sorelya-faq]').forEach(function (faq) {\n      var items = faq.querySelectorAll('[data-sorelya-faq-item]');\n\n      items.forEach(function (item) {\n        var trigger = item.querySelector('.sorelya-faq__trigger');\n\n        if (!trigger) return;\n\n        trigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');\n\n        trigger.addEventListener('click', function () {\n          var wasOpen = item.classList.contains('open');\n\n          items.forEach(function (otherItem) {\n            otherItem.classList.remove('open');\n\n            var otherTrigger = otherItem.querySelector(\n              '.sorelya-faq__trigger'\n            );\n\n            if (otherTrigger) {\n              otherTrigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');\n            }\n          });\n\n          if (!wasOpen) {\n            item.classList.add('open');\n            trigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');\n          }\n        });\n      });\n    });\n  })();\n</script>",
        "background": "",
        "background_gradient": "",
        "text_color": ""
      }
    },
    "faq_aX8Tqy": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_AxYrhi": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Verstecken sie Cellulite wirklich oder glätten sie nur ein bisschen?",
            "content": "<p>Sie VERSTECKEN sie. Vollständig. Der Kompressionsstoff wirkt wie ein Instagram-Filter für deine Beine — Cellulite, Äderchen, Narben, Dehnungsstreifen verschwinden einfach. Du bekommst makellos gleichmäßige Beine. Anders als normale Strumpfhosen die jede Unebenheit zeigen, glättet Sorelyaas Shaping-Technologie die Hauttextur und erhält dabei die natürliche Optik. Stell es dir vor wie Photoshop zum Anziehen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_YVPrFj": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Brauche ich noch Shapewear darunter?",
            "content": "<p>Nein. Sorelya hat eine integrierte Formkontrolle von der Taille bis zum Oberschenkel. Das hochhüftige Kompressionsband flacht den Bauch ab und betont die Taille wie ein 40€-Shapewear — aber ohne die extra Schicht oder sichtbare Wäscheabdrücke. Sofortige Schlankheitswirkung ohne mehrere Produkte übereinander. Ein Paar übernimmt die Arbeit von Strumpfhose + Shapewear + Wärme. Endlich.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_cFtpRw": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Wie lange hält der formende Effekt an?",
            "content": "<p>Er lässt nicht nach. Die Kompression ist in die Faserstruktur eingebaut, kein Coating das sich rauswäscht. Wir haben diese durch über 200 Waschzyklen getestet — die Formkraft bleibt konstant. Wenn Kundinnen sagen \"noch wie neu nach 6 Monaten\" meinen sie auch das Shaping, nicht nur die Haltbarkeit. Sollte das Kontrollband je an Elastizität verlieren, greift unsere Lebenslange Ersatzgarantie.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_eT3eQK": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Sieht man sie unter engen Kleidern oder Röcken?",
            "content": "<p>Nein. Sie sind so konzipiert, dass sie selbst unter den figurbetontesten Kleidungsstücken unsichtbar bleiben. Keine sichtbaren Nähte, keine Wäscheabdrücke, kein verräterischer Bund. Die Einzel-Naht-Konstruktion hinten eliminiert Volumen während die nahtlosen Seiten komplett flach anliegen. Du kannst sie mit deinem engsten Bleistiftrock oder Bodycon-Kleid tragen — niemand kennt dein Geheimnis.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_tAYcr8": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Was passiert wenn ich mich bücke oder sitze?",
            "content": "<p>Volle Abdeckung aus jedem Winkel. Die Deckkraft ist strategisch abgestuft — dicker am Körper, transparent an den Füßen. Beim Bücken, Sitzen oder Bewegen behält der Stoff volle Abdeckung ohne durchsichtig zu werden. Mehrere Kundinnen haben das buchstäblich mit Spiegelfotos getestet (ihre Worte, nicht unsere 😅). Totales Vertrauen, null Garderobe-Pannen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_K9DezK": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Halten sie auch bei echter Kälte warm?",
            "content": "<p>Bewertet bis -23°C. Das ist echter Winterfrost, kein leichter Herbstwind. Das Fleece-Futter erzeugt eine Wärmebarriere die Körperwärme wie Winterhosen einsperrt — von außen siehst du jedoch aus als trägst du normale Strumpfhosen. Du kannst Kleider im Januar in Berlin tragen und dabei wirklich warm sein. Wichtig: Die Füße sind transparent (nicht gefüttert) damit sie in Stiefeln nicht überhitzen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_A6K9UF": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Ich bin groß (1,72m+) — sind sie lang genug?",
            "content": "<p>Nimm eine Größe größer wenn du 1,72m oder größer bist. Unsere Größen basieren zwar auf dem Gewicht, aber die Körpergröße beeinflusst die Schrittnähte. Im Zweifelsfall immer größer wählen — die Formwirkung bleibt vollständig erhalten.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_HXkUiJ": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Warum kosten diese 40€ wenn es Strumpfhosen für 10€ gibt?",
            "content": "<p>Weil 10€-Strumpfhosen nicht das können was Sorelya kann. Günstige Thermostrumpfhosen geben dir Wärme. Sorelya gibt dir :</p><ul><li>Wärme bis -23°C</li><li>Geformte Kurven (kein Abflachungseffekt)</li><li>Cellulite-Versteckung</li><li>Sofortige Schlankheitswirkung</li><li>Nackte-Haut-Illusion</li><li>Lebenslange Haltbarkeit</li></ul><p>So siehts aus: Du gibst 120€/Jahr für 10€-Strumpfhosen die ständig reißen. Oder einmal 39.99€ für Strumpfhosen die mehrere Winter halten UND dich unglaublich aussehen lassen. Dazu kommt unsere Lebenslange Ersatzgarantie — wenn sie je reißen, schicken wir kostenlos neue. Für immer. <strong>Investition statt Ausgabe.</strong></p>"
          }
